complaint_text: Received batch with visible solder voids on 12% of units. Connector pads show incomplete wetting, affecting reliability.
Biosensor strips exhibit inconsistent electrode thickness. Measured values range from 45 to 78 nm versus spec 50-60 nm.
Multiple connectors show bent pins after unpacking. 8 out of 200 units affected. Suspect packaging issue.
Dimensional check failed: flex circuit width 5.12 mm vs specification 5.00 +/- 0.05 mm. Entire lot rejected.
High resistance measured on PCB trace between pads 3 and 7. Values 2.3 ohm vs max 0.5 ohm spec.
Foreign particle contamination found under microscope on 3 biosensor assemblies. Particles appear metallic.
Cold solder joints observed on flex connector terminals. Pull test failures at 1.2 N vs minimum 2.0 N requirement.
Connector housing shows crack after thermal cycling test. Failure at 150 cycles vs 500 cycle requirement.
Short circuit detected between adjacent traces on PCB module. 5 out of 100 units affected in incoming inspection.
Cytotoxicity test failed for biosensor assembly. Cell viability dropped to 62% vs minimum 80% requirement per ISO 10993.
Surface oxidation visible on gold-plated contacts. Discoloration noted on approximately 20% of connector pads.
Received wrong quantity: PO specified 5000 units, shipment contained only 4200. Packing list shows 5000.
Delamination observed on PCB module after reflow soldering. Layers separating at edges of 15% of boards.
Warpage on flex connector exceeds 0.3 mm vs max 0.1 mm specification. Assembly line rejection rate increased to 8%.
Labeling error: lot number on box does not match lot number on individual biosensor packaging. Traceability concern.
Misalignment of connector pins. Pin pitch measured 0.52 mm vs nominal 0.50 mm. Mating with PCB socket fails.
Solder bridging between adjacent pads on flex connector. Electrical short detected during final test.
Residue observed on PCB surface after cleaning. Ionic contamination test shows 2.1 ug/cm2 NaCl eq. vs max 1.56.
Sensitization concern raised after patient reported mild skin reaction near biosensor application site.
Damage in transit: 3 reels of flex connectors arrived with crushed packaging. Visual inspection shows bent leads on outer layers.
Solder void defects detected on flex connector batch. X-ray inspection shows voids exceeding 25% of pad area on Line 2 production.
Cold solder joints found on microconnector terminals produced on Line 2. Failure rate 15% in pull testing.
Insufficient solder on flex connector pads. Solder paste volume approximately 40% below nominal. Line 2 production run.
Open circuit detected on PCB module trace. Suspect solder reflow issue on Line 2. 8% failure rate at ICT.
Solder bridging on fine-pitch flex connector pads. Multiple shorts between 0.3 mm pitch pads. Line 2 batch.
Electrode delamination on biosensor strip. Adhesion test shows peel strength 0.8 N/cm vs minimum 1.5 N/cm.
Cold solder on flex connector batch from Line 2. Visual inspection shows dull, grainy solder joints on 22% of units.
Connector pins out of tolerance. Length variation +/- 0.08 mm vs spec +/- 0.02 mm. Mating force excessive.
Irritation reported by end user at device contact point. Biocompatibility retest requested per ISO 10993-10.
Foreign particle found embedded in flex circuit dielectric layer. Particle analysis pending. Production halted for investigation.
